=E2=80=94<strong>Riccardo Tisci</strong>, too=E2=80=94but
it=E2=80=99s <strong>Sarah Burton</strong>=E2=80=99s time now, and this era=
 of her career is not about preserving the legacy of her predecessors (incl=
uding longtime collaborator <strong>Alexander McQueen</strong>). Nope, this=
 was all about Burton, and what she thinks should define the house of <stro=
ng>Hubert de Givenchy</strong>: curved shoulders, big bows, clean tailoring=
, and cocktail dresses for hot women who love wearing black and trendy thin=
gs. LVMH needs more brands that lead with the clothes, and this
was that.</li></ul></div>
